<TITLE> UN to help get back laundered money </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 4 (bdnews24.com) - The United Nations has promised technical assistance to help Bangladesh bring back money laundered from the country. "We provide technical assistance on terrorist financing. ..One of our technical bodies may also give assistance to countries interested to bring laundered money back from abroad," said Sergey Karev, director of assessment and technical assistance, Counter Terrorism Committee of the UN Executive Directorate. Karev, now in Dhaka, made the statement after a meeting with Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed at his office Monday. Karev said that his office could extend legal assistance in this regard. "If a country wants to bring laundered money back from another country, our technical body can extend help," he said. However, Salehuddin Ahmed said that bringing siphoned off money back was a 'complex and time consuming matter.' "We are in progress on the issue. But it mainly depends on the laws of a respective country," Ahmed said. "We will have to sign agreements with the financial intelligence units of other countries to get information on money laundering and terrorist financing," he said. BB recently announced formation of FIU. The central bank governor also pointed to the necessity of government assistance as well as efficiency in this regard. bd
